US President Barack Obama said on Saturday that diplomacy was the best option to deal with Iran 's contested nuclear program , two days after the conclusion of a framework agreement with Tehran .
Iran and six world powers determined the outlines of a landmark agreement which would curb Iran ' ' nuclear program and potentially lift economic sanctions .
Obama said he expects a ` robust debate ' on the deal .
Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu says this agreement would ` threaten the state of Israel .